-- Billy King of 76ers Named General Manager of NBA's Nets, Replacing Thorn
-- Jay Beberman
-- 2010-07-14T17:05:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/billy-king-of-76ers-named-general-manager-of-nba-s-nets-replacing-thorn.html

          
          
             The New Jersey Nets named Billy King
general manager, replacing Rod Thorn.  
 King spent 10 years with the Philadelphia 76ers, serving as
president from 2003-2007.  
 Thorn said last month he would be leaving the National
Basketball Association team on July 15.  
          
          


  


        